Anne Bowden, his mother, influenced his early life, and John Coleridge, his father, was a lawyer and a friend of the poet William Wordsworth, which also had an impact on Coleridge. The scores are divided equally as both parents played a role in his upbringing and development as a poet.

Q: what are the catholic holy days?
A:

RESULT: 
The Catholic Church observes several holy days throughout the year. Some of the most important ones include:

1. Christmas (December 25) - Celebrates the birth of Jesus Christ.
2. Easter (date varies each year) - Commemorates the resurrection of Jesus Christ.
3. Ascension of the Lord (40 days after Easter) - Marks Jesus' ascension into heaven.
4. Pentecost (50 days after Easter) - Celebrates the descent of the Holy Spirit upon the apostles.
5. All Saints' Day (November 1) - Honors all the saints, known and unknown.
6. All Souls' Day (November 2) - A day of prayer for the souls of the faithful departed.
7. Immaculate Conception (December 8) - Celebrates the belief that Mary was conceived without original sin.
8. Assumption of the Blessed Virgin Mary (August 15) - Marks the belief that Mary was taken up body and soul into heaven.

These are just a few of the major holy days in the Catholic Church. There are also numerous feasts, memorials, and obligatory days of fasting and abstinence throughout the liturgical year.

Q: what did michael crabtree do?
A:

RESULT: 
Michael Crabtree is a former American football wide receiver who played in the National Football League (NFL) for 11 seasons. He was drafted by the San Francisco 49ers in the first round of the 2009 NFL Draft. Crabtree played college football at Texas Tech University. During his professional career, he was known for his route-running ability and his knack for making big plays in crucial moments. After his time with the 49ers, Crabtree also played for the Oakland Raiders and the Baltimore Ravens.
